<HEADLINE>
GOVERNMENT TO DEVELOP CENTRAL, SOUTHERN TAIWAN: PREMIER
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March 16 (CNA) 03/16/07  21:31:31 (By T.C. Jiang)
</P>
<P>
Premier Su Tseng-chang has vowed to step up infrastructure
construction in central and southern Taiwan as part of efforts to
boost the economies of those areas.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came after Su met with central Taiwan city and county
chiefs at aseminar held in Taichung City Thursday. Also present
at the seminar were Vice Premier Tsai Ing-wen, Interior Minister
Lee Yi-yang, Minister of Economic Affairs Chen Ruey-long,
Minister of Transportation and Communications Tsai Duei, Council
for Economic Planning and Development Chairwoman Ho Mei-yueh and
Council of Labor Affairs Chairman Lee Ying-yuan.
</P>
<P>
Miaoli county officials urged the government to ease the limit on
the number of households that are allowed to build roads for
agricultural use, a spokesman for the seminar said, adding that
Nantou county officials expressed hope that a tapwater facility
can be constructed on the Chingjing veteran's farm and called for
more budget for the purchase of vehicles for township chiefs.
</P>
<P>
Changhua county officials expressed hope that more art and
cultural centers can be established in the central county and
that the Central Taiwan Science Park can be expanded to the
county, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Yunlin county officials said they want a high-speed rail station
in the southern county, while Taichung county officials asked the
government to build large parks, large exhibition centers, a
large airport and a subway system in the central city, and to
assist in the prevention and eradication of biting insects.
</P>
<P>
In response, the premier said the government will begin to seek
balanced development in the cities and counties of Taiwan and
promised to help improve the infrastructure in the center and
south.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he called on the local chiefs to support his "Mega
Investment, Mega Warmth" economic stimulus project in order to
achieve this goal.
</P>
